{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"78881751-0224-44f4-88e7-b7943d2237ec","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\n**Then verify:**\n```bash\ndotnet --version        # confirm 11.0.100\ndotnet build            # ensure it compiles\ndotnet test             # run tests\n```\n\nAlso check for any NuGet packages (e.g. `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.Extensions.*`) that need version bumps to their .NET 11 releases.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"db9db83b-b505-46c8-bf9c-b4a874b23b5a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no need to explore their codebase since they've described the files involved.","outputTokens":299,"requestId":"B00C:14B60F:191697:1D98B5:69F2B441"},"id":"c05c456d-13f7-49ef-b01f-523008a0cfb1","timestamp":"2026-04-30T01:45:44.481Z","parentId":"995cff32-c536-4ee8-a3b4-9b7efc9261ec"}
